Below is a **fully-scaffolded, minute-by-minute plan for Week 1 of Term 2**
(**Monday 1 December – Friday 5 December**) in Grade 1 Early French Immersion.
It mirrors the Term 1 day-plans you liked:

* **Daily “why”** → explicit PEI Grade-1 outcome reference.
* **Timed schedule grid** (08 :30 – 14 :00) with **Key moves & materials** and **Assessment / differentiation** every block.
* **End-of-day Prep lists** keep workload transparent.

Curriculum links: PEI Grade-1 French-Immersion & Mathematics guides ([princeedwardisland.ca][1], [princeedwardisland.ca][2], [princeedwardisland.ca][3]), KidsHealth winter-safety resources ([kidshealth.org][4], [kidshealth.org][5], [kidshealth.org][6]).

---

## WEEK FOCUS

| Strand             | Week-1 Target                                                                            |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **FLA**            | Review Term-1 graphemes ➜ introduce consonant blend **gn**; sight-word **il y a**        |
| **Math**           | Place value to **30** (tens & ones), skip-count by 5s                                    |
| **Science**        | Launch **Bean-in-a-Bag** germination inquiry (Needs of Living Things)                    |
| **Social Studies** | Begin **Our Local Community** unit – co-create classroom map legend                      |
| **Health**         | Winter-clothing layers & frostbite prevention ([kidshealth.org][4], [kidshealth.org][6]) |
| **Arts**           | Radial-symmetry **snow-flake collage** (line, shape, balance)                            |

---

### MONDAY 1 DEC — “Gn comme cygne”

| Time                | Block                                                                                                                                                               | Key moves & materials                                                       | Assessment / differentiation |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| **08 :30 – 08 :45** | **Accueil & Chant** – feelings check; sound-review rap (Term-1 blends).                                                                                             | Note any student consistently choosing “sad” card → SEL follow-up.          |                              |
| **08 :45 – 09 :15** | **FLA 1 (GCO 2)** – mouth-mirror demo **/ɲ/ gn**; chant “gn-gn-cy-gne”; air-trace “gn”. Students sand-tray write gn.                                                | ✓ Every child voices a gn word; teacher ticklist for articulation accuracy. |                              |
| **09 :15 – 09 :35** | **FLA 2** – Big-book **« L’hiver arrive »** pp. 1-3; echo-read, clap on **gn** & sight-phrase **il y a**.                                                           | Anecdotal: one-to-one tracking & pointer use.                               |                              |
| **09 :45 – 10 :30** | **Mathematics (1.N.1)** – “Count-around” to 30 with snow-ball plush; build 30 using 3 tens-sticks + 0 ones; T-chart tens/ones anchor. Exit sticky: represent 18.    | Collect stickies; pull small group tomorrow if “tens/ones” reversed.        |                              |
| **10 :45 – 11 :30** | **Science (SCO 205-1)** – **Bean-in-a-Bag** demo: damp-towel, 3 beans, label “Jour 0”. Staple bag half-way, tape to sunny window.                                   | Pictogram sheet ✓: circle needed items (eau, lumière, air).                 |                              |
| **12 :45 – 13 :15** | **Health (W-1.6)** – Winter-layers mini-lesson: base / mid / outer (KidsHealth slide). Sort clothing cards into 3 hoops. ([kidshealth.org][4], [kidshealth.org][5]) | Ask 2 students to dress felt figure in correct layers – quick rubric.       |                              |
| **13 :15 – 14 :00** | **Art (VA 1.1)** – Fold 8-point square, snip radial cuts → open “flake”; glue on navy paper; sprinkle salt + blue wash for ice effect.                              | Peer “Wow / Wonder” sticky on gallery line.                                 |                              |

*Prep tonight*: copy “il y a” word-wall strip, laminate clothing cards, pre-fold 25 snow-flake squares.

---

### TUESDAY 2 DEC — “Il y a un cygne !”

| Time          | Block                                                                                       | Key moves                                  | Assessment |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ---------- |
| 08 :30-08 :50 | Review chant gn + write **il y a** on mini-boards.                                          | ✓ boards checked for spacing / capitals.   |            |
| 08 :50-09 :30 | **Guided Reading** *Décode 3* (gn focus); highlight tape on **il y a**.                     | Running-record slot 11.                    |            |
| 09 :30-10 :10 | **Math** – Counting **11-20** tens/ones snap-cubes; students fill “What’s my value?” sheet. | Teacher confer; note who mis-groups tens.  |            |
| 10 :25-11 :05 | **Science** – Observe beans (likely unchanged); model “0 cm” ruler line.                    | Journals: draw bag, write *“Il y a 0 cm.”* |            |
| 12 :45-13 :15 | **SS** – Brainstorm familiar community spots; co-create icon legend (maison, école, parc).  | Photo legend for reference.                |            |
| 13 :15-14 :00 | **Arts** – Cool-colour wet-on-wet wash for yesterday’s flakes; sprinkle coarse salt.        | Observation of brush grip / water control. |            |

*Prep*: cut snap-cubes bundles; print value sheets; charge doc-cam.

---

### WEDNESDAY 3 DEC — “Skip 5, hop to 30”

| Time          | Block                                                                                                                                     | Key moves                                                             | Assessment |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| 08 :30-08 :50 | Feelings + *gn* flash-quiz; quick sight-phrase relay (*il y a*).                                                                          |                                                                       |            |
| 08 :50-09 :30 | **FLA** – Pocket-chart sentence stretch: *« Il y a un cygne blanc »* → add adjective card. Students create own lines.                     | Teacher snapshot for writing wall.                                    |            |
| 09 :40-10 :25 | **Math** – Skip-count by 5s snowball toss (5-10-15-…-30); build 5-groups bead chains. ✓                                                   | Exit card: write next three numbers after 20 when skip-counting by 5. |            |
| 10 :40-11 :20 | **Science** – Magnify bean (doc-cam); label *tégument*.                                                                                   | Journals: trace grain & label.                                        |            |
| 12 :45-13 :25 | **Health** – Frostbite signs: show KidsHealth pics (white, numb) ([kidshealth.org][4], [kidshealth.org][6]); role-play glove/hat choices. | Thumbs-up / side test.                                                |            |
| 13 :25-14 :00 | **Art** – Add silver marker accents to flakes; mount on bulletin board “Nos flocons”.                                                     | Peer “Symmetry scan” talk partner.                                    |            |

*Prep*: string bead chains; print frostbite sign cards.

---

### THURSDAY 4 DEC — “Mon sac, mes haricots grandissent ?”

| Time          | Block                                                                                              | Key moves                                 | Assessment |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| 08 :30-08 :50 | Warm-up: sentence scramble race with **il y a** cards.                                             |                                           |            |
| 08 :50-09 :30 | **Dictée** 6 items – 3 gn words / 3 sentences incl. *il y a*.                                      | Mark for accent & spacing.                |            |
| 09 :40-10 :25 | **Math** – Place-value **mystery number bag**: pull tens-stick + ones cubes, peers write number. ✓ | Teacher anecdotal who reverses digits.    |            |
| 10 :40-11 :20 | **Science** – Measure beans (may show bump 0.5 cm); add to class line-plot.                        | Students shade bar graph °C vs sprout cm. |            |
| 12 :45-13 :15 | **SS** – Start large classroom-floor map: tape outline + legend icons.                             | Photo progress.                           |            |
| 13 :15-14 :00 | **Health ART** – Design winter-layer posters (3 flap lift-the-layer).                              | Gallery sticky “One new thing I learned”. |            |

*Prep*: load mystery bags, copy bar-graph sheet, tape floor map borders.

---

### FRIDAY 5 DEC — “Carte de notre communauté”

| Time          | Block                                                                                                                                                        | Key moves                                      | Assessment |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| 08 :30-09 :00 | **FLA** – Reader’s-theatre reprise pages 4-6 “L’hiver arrive”; video on tablet.                                                                              | Rubric expression & pacing.                    |            |
| 09 :00-09 :30 | **FLA** – Students write 2-sentence caption under recording using **il y a** + gn word.                                                                      | Teacher quick-check; send to Seesaw.           |            |
| 09 :40-10 :30 | **Math “Show What You Know”** – Station rotation:<br>① Tens/ones build 23, 17, 30 (photo)<br>② Skip-5 hop mat to 50<br>③ Matching cards numeral ↔ tens/ones. | Sticker charts; note mastery gaps.             |            |
| 10 :45-11 :15 | **Science** – Discuss which seed germinated fastest; wonder-wall questions.                                                                                  | Collect journals for weekend look-over.        |            |
| 12 :45-13 :15 | **SS** – Finish floor map; students walk “route to school desk” using legend words. ✓                                                                        | Anecdotal vocabulary use.                      |            |
| 13 :15-14 :00 | **Art / Celebration** – Paper-snowball toss gallery walk; each reads one peer caption out loud.                                                              | Exit ticket: draw one thing learned this week. |            |

*Prep (weekend)*: Mark math station sheets; review bean journals; upload theatre video link to parents.

