| ----------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **FLA**     | Sand-trays, “gn” flashcards, sight-phrase strips (*il y a*), mini-books “L’hiver arrive” & “Mon panda”, pocket-chart sentence pieces. |
| **Math**    | Tens-sticks (3 × 30), loose cubes, place-value mats, bead chains of 5, open-number cards, skip-5 hop mat, station sticker charts.     |
| **Science** | 30 zip-bags, paper-towels, dried beans, rulers, line-plot chart, doc-cam.                                                             |
| **SS**      | Icon legend cards, coloured masking tape for floor map.                                                                               |
| **Health**  | Layer-clothing picture cards, KidsHealth frostbite posters.                                                                           |
| **Art**     | 15 cm squares (snow-flakes), navy cardstock, coarse salt, liquid water-colour, silver markers, display staples.                       |

This detailed plan launches Term 2 with **fresh phonics, robust place-value work, an engaging germination inquiry, winter-safety lessons, and a visually striking snow-flake project** while collecting daily formative evidence for January progress notes. Enjoy the frosty fun! ([princeedwardisland.ca][1], [princeedwardisland.ca][2], [princeedwardisland.ca][3], [kidshealth.org][4], [kidshealth.org][5], [kidshealth.org][6])

