They mirror the depth, timing and layout of the Week 1 outline you approved, and continue the curricular trajectory set in your Term-2 overview:

| Strand             | Week 2 Target                                                       | Week 3 Target                                                                 |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **FLA**            | Phonics **oi** + sight-word **voici**; begin patterned poem writing | Phonics **eau/au** + sight-word **voilà**; draft 3-sentence winter narratives |
| **Math**           | Place value **31 – 40**; skip-count by **5s to 50**                 | Place value **41 – 50**; near-doubles / make-10 addition & subtraction        |
| **Science**        | Track bean height; compare **plant vs animal needs**                | Begin **light-source & shadow** investigations                                |
| **Social Studies** | Classroom-map legend → **community-helper centre role-play**        | Make simple street-map routes & symbols                                       |
| **Health**         | 24-hr activity log → set **active-living goal**                     | **Winter-safety** refresher & belly-breathing routine                         |
| **Arts**           | Cool-colour wash “icy landscapes”                                   | Print-making **animal tracks in snow**                                        |

Curriculum links draw on the same PEI Grade-1 guides and KidsHealth / Canada Food-Guide resources cited earlier.

