## WEEK 4 (Mon 5 Jan – Fri 9 Jan)

### Week-focus table

| Strand             | This-week target                                                                                                            |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **FLA**            | Phonics **eu** + question-words **qui / où / quoi**; write a 4-sentence descriptive paragraph with colour & size adjectives |
| **Math**           | Place value **41-50**; rods & units; expanded form                                                                          |
| **Science**        | Explore **light sources** – natural vs artificial                                                                           |
| **Social Studies** | Build **Past ↔ Present communication timeline**                                                                             |
| **Health**         | Tooth-brushing demo + germ-glitter station                                                                                  |
| **Arts**           | **Shadow-silhouette murals** (contrast & line)                                                                              |

---

### Monday 5 Jan — “Eu comme feu”

| Time        | Block                                                                                                                  | Key moves & materials                                 | Assessment / differentiation |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| 08:30-08:45 | Greeting & feelings; mouth-mirror **/ø/** ➜ chant “Eu-eu-feu”.                                                         | Flag any articulation miscues for Tuesday mini-group. |                              |
| 08:45-09:15 | **FLA-1** (GCO 2) – air-trace *eu*; mini-book **« Feu de camp »**; intro Q-word **qui**.                               | ✓ Each child reads 1 page; pointer use noted.         |                              |
| 09:15-09:35 | **FLA-2** – pocket-chart sentence *« Qui a du feu bleu ? »*; pupils swap colour adjectives.                            | Anecdotal for adjective agreement.                    |                              |
| 09:45-10:30 | **Math (1.N.1)** – build **41-45** with 4 rods + ones cubes; record expanded 40 + 5. Exit sticky: show 47.             | Collect stickies, target reteach group.               |                              |
| 10:45-11:30 | **Science (205-1)** – “Light Hunt”: flashlight off; pupils tag natural vs artificial pictures posted. T-chart sorting. | Photo chart; sticker ✓ for correct choice.            |                              |
| 12:45-13:15 | **Health (KidsHealth)** – giant teeth model; brush 2-min song; germ-glitter lotion UV check                            | Graph clean vs germy spots.                           |                              |
| 13:15-14:00 | **Art (VA 1.1)** – partner flashlight trace side-profile on large paper (silhouette).                                  | Teacher note partner co-operation.                    |                              |

